{
  "texts": [
    "Their goal was to minimize the total cost of allocating personnel to skills, penalties for tardiness, and pre-emption fees.",
    "They suggested two integer programming formulations and created an ant colony-based metaheuristic to address the model's real world problems of large scale.",
    "Many studies have addressed staffing scheduling problems with time considerations.",
    "Karam et al. [109] developed a MILP model for a flexible working hours integrated project scheduling and multi-skilled workforce allocation problem.",
    "The model considers the assignment of scarce workers with varying skill levels and efficiencies to tasks with variable skill requirements and durations.Additionally, the model incorporates flexible working hours and effective team building to develop workers' skills through knowledge transfer."
  ]
}